cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with stereo matching and image-to-image translation. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of unsupervised learning, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The application of the method to tracking, recognition, and detection suggests that it could also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of cross-spectral data and image pairs suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
